title: For Sale:  IAB Italian O/U 12GA Shotgun
location: Boynton Beach, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent: IAB Italian Over/Under 12GA Shotgun.  29.5" Fixed Choke Barrels.  Top Barrel is "FULL CHOKE", Bottom Barrel is "MODIFIED CHOKE".  Shotgun is in excellent condition with minor handling marks. This is a beautifully made Italian shotgun, that is not manufactured anymore.  The Russian Shooting Team used IAB shotguns during the 70's & 80's, winning many gold and silver medals.  This shotgun is not "Hammer" fired, it is "Striker" fired, and as such does not have a selector for the "Over" or "Under" barrel to fire.  The Lower (Under) barrel will always fire first.  The shotgun has auto ejectors, but the timing is slightly off on the Lower barrel ejector.  Other then that, the shotgun functions flawlessly. I had a Gunsmith fully check the shotgun within the past month.  I have added a high rise front and rear fiber optic sights.  The inside of the barrels have a very high gloss mirror finish. The shotgun shows very little wear, and apparently had very little use. title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer P226 Elite
postcontent: Hey! I won't drone on with a long description of the basic features of this pistol, as I feel the Elite series from Sig basically speaks for itself. Hell, the P226 platform by itself, without any of the fancy up-market features of the Elite series, is an absolutely fantastic pistol. Google/YouTube search "Sig P226 review" if you would like to see a mountain of lengthy and glowing reviews on this series of pistols.Anyway, up for sale today is my P226 Elite, my favorite pistol that I've ever owned. I am the first owner of this gun, which was purchased new in 2009. It has almost 2000 rounds on the clock. It has been absolutely flawless in all that time, and is without question my first choice as a nightstand/roadtrip gun. I trust it with my life. Why am I selling it, then? I got a Legion P226 as a gift, and now this one seems redundant. So there are a few negatives, all related to the fact that I never saw myself selling this gun until now. This thing has traveled all over the country with me and functioned as a pack gun and a go-to HD pistol on and off for years. I have done my best to avoid abusing it, but it has most certainly been used. Basically, if you're the sort of person who can't handle buying a used gun with a bit of holster wear and a few scratches here and there, turn back now. If you want a proven pistol that is fully broken-in for a couple hundred bucks cheaper than retail, here it is!Bad: it's got VERY MINOR finish wear in all the normal spots you would expect from holstering, barrel crown finish wear from shooting, and has a handful of surface scratches (nothing actually deep in the finish, they look like light pencil marks). The rosewood grips (yes, I have those too) have one long-ish scratch on them from when I used to carry it in my pack with those grips installed before I bought the Hogues you see in the pic. I do NOT have the box for it, I lost that in my last move...I never thought it would matter because I thought I'd never be selling this gun, but here we are. I can only include ONE MAGAZINE with the pistol, which is the 15rd factory mag. That is the only mag that came with the gun when I bought it, I have a bunch of MecGar mags, but they're all pre-ban and cannot be legally transferred with the gun...also I want to keep them for my new pistol.  Good: it's a Sig P226 Elite. The trigger is butter, the night sights are still extremely bright, and to whatever degree a pistol like this needs to be broken in, it has been. This thing is good to go, load it up and bet your life that it'll work when it needs to and put all rounds on target faster and more intuitively than anything besides a competition-built 1911. It is the most natural-shooting pistol I own, no contest. I will include both the Hogue grips in the picture as well as the factory rosewood grips, plus I'll throw in a zip-up pistol pouch in an attempt to compensate for the lack of a box. Please don't hesitate to email me with any further questions, I will be happy to answer them. I sell on here a lot, and I pride myself on collecting/trading/selling quality guns. I don't buy junk, I don't sell junk, this is a damn nice pistol and the only reason I'm getting rid of it is because it's being replaced by a newer version of the exact same gun. My normal FFL is in Littleton, but buyer pays transfer so I'll meet anywhere in the Denver/Boulder orbit for no extra charge...+$25 for me to drive as far as Summit County, CO Springs or into the mountains as far as Fairplay/Idaho Springs/Nederland/etc, +$50 for anywhere further within the state. Thanks for checking it out! Again, email only for any/all enquiries.
